1 CLANCREATE~
This help is intended for high level players intending to create their
own clan. To do so is not a simple task as there are many things which
you must think about.

Name:      the clan must have a name! Ideally a few words long. Avoid
           putting in words which are existing races, classes or even
           clans(!) and it must be able to be prepended by the word 'the'.
           You could have 'Brotherhood of Schmee', but could not have
           'the Eagle Clerics'.

Ranks:     you must come up with five distinct clan rank names. See help
           clanrank.

Whoname:   this is what is seen on the who list before a member's name
           and should be no more than five characters long.
Theme
& History:
           there must be a general theme to the clan, e.g. military,
           magical, chaotic, druidic etc. This must be explained in a
           few paragraphs of text. The more detail the better, as this
           adds depth to the roleplaying aspect of clans.

Rooms:     you must create a few clan rooms to start out with (with potential
           for expansion later). These will have a financial cost, details
           of this will be explained to you. One of the rooms will be the
           'recall clan' point.

Objects:   you must create several clan objects which members will be
           encouraged to wear. The 'stats' (e.g. armour class, bonuses for
           characteristics etc) cannot be too good and, like any other piece
           of equipment on the mud, will be influenced by level.

To create rooms and objects requires you to know how to code using the Xania
Area Writing format. If you have e-mail then you can be sent the appropriate
document for explaining how to do this. This document may also be on the
Xania web page soon (http://www.pyro.org/). Speak to an implementor soon
about your ideas and to learn how to submit your clan application.
~

1 CLANCHANNELS~	
Syntax:   |Gclantalk <message>|w
Shortcut: |G> <message>|w

The communication channels of Xania are all based on a telepathic network
which is supported by the Gods. If you use the 'gossip' channel, for
example, you transmit a telepathic message which gets relayed via the
Gods and transmitted to all denizens of Xania, if they chose to hear it.

When engaging in private communications, e.g. when using 'tell', you are
using your own psychic capabilities to transmit the message, and similarly,
when you are grouped, 'group tell' requires a group effort.

In recent times, the Gods decided to give certain individuals the ability to
support their own private communications network. This 'clan channel' ability
has fallen upon those who create and lead clans. Those who hold a high
standing within a clan can also support the clan channel.

If a clan leader or clan hero is present in the lands of Xania, then they
act as a |Wtelepathic nexus|w by which messages sent by members of the clan
get relayed to all other members. If no leader or clan hero is present, then
no telepathic nexus exists, and any effort you may make to use the clan
channel will be futile.

Clan leaders and heroes are responsible for what is sent on the clan channels,
as it is by their very presence that the channel can actually function. See
help NOCLANCHAN.
~

1 CLANFUNDS~
For the present, clan leaders and heroes may collect money for the benefit
of their clan and store it in the form of the unique clan gems. These gems
are only available from immortals and are worth $500,000. If you wish to
exchange this amount of gold for a gem, you must wait until a God is present
and willing to provide you with a piece of the sacred krellstone. Keepers
of the gems are responsible for looking after them; if you lose them or they
get destroyed then you have lost a significant store of wealth. Keep them
in a protected container! It will be possible to use these funds for the
purposes of buying objects, rooms and other things, for the clan.
~


1 CLANLEADER~
This help file is meant for those who hold the (default) rank of leader
in their clan.

You are the most powerful individual in your clan and therefore hold a
degree of responsibility for its actions. The clan channel is a right which
has been granted to you as a favour from the Gods and it is up to you
to keep tabs on what is said upon it. If you intend to give a member of your
clan the rank of 'hero', keep in mind the fact that this rank gives them
the ability to activate the clan channel, and gives them the noclanchan
command too.

Promotion or demotion of members of your clan is at your own discretion, but
the following guidelines should be maintained: (see help ClanRank)

       Rank      Number of Clan Members
---------------------------------------
       Leader    1
       Hero      2       Note: use of the promote and demote command
       Adept     5             is logged, so don't think you can get
       Initiate  any           away with promoting and demoting members
       Member    any           regularly.

As clan leader, you have final say in what rooms, equipment etc is
submitted to the implementors. However, you should encourage all active
members to make an input - it should not be a 'one man clan' situation.

There will probably be more to come here, watch this space!
~

