1 CLANRANKS~
Each clan has its own discrete ranks, the name of each being based on the
nature of the clan. However, the highest rank in a clan, is generally
referred to as the '|Rleader|w' and one rank below leader is '|Rclan hero|w'.
Each clan has five default clan ranks.

example:
Clan: Warriors of Kai

    Default Rank      Rank Name (unique to this clan)
    -------------------------------------------------
(1) Clan Leader       Patriarch
(2) Clan Hero         Kai-Lord
(3) Adept             Kai-Crusader
(4) Initiate          Kai-Rider
(5) Member            Kai-Intrepid

Only those ranked Clan Leader can use the |Wmember|w or |Wpromote|w commands.
Only those ranked Clan Hero or higher allow the clan channel to be active.
~

1 CLANWEB~
Clans can have their own web pages, courtesy of pyro.org ;) If you are a leader
or a member of a clan, you may come up with some clan related info which can
be placed on the page.

Typical stuff would include the fantasy history of your clan, legendary
members, the clan's objectives and as much roleplaying stuff as possible.

You don't have to write the pages in html format, just leave a note to immortal
or speak to an implementor and you will be told how to submit clan web pages.

It is possible to tie your clan web page in with your own characters web
page (see 'help web').
~

1 CLANWHO~
Typing 'clanwho' will show you all of the visible members of your clan who
are currently logged on, along with their clan rank. You cannot use it to
see members and ranks of other clans.~



1 MEMBER~
Syntax: member + <player name>
        member - <player name>

This is used by clan leaders to make a player a member of their clan, or to
remove an existing member.
~

1 PROMOTE DEMOTE~
Syntax: promote <clan member name>
        demote  <clan member name>

This can be used by clan leaders to promote or demote the status of an existing
clan member. The default number of 'ranks' in a clan is 5. There can only ever
be a single leader who holds this command.
~

1 NOCLANCHAN~
Syntax: noclanchan <clan member name>

This is used to remove a clan member's right to use the clan channel. Members
of a clan who allow the channel to function i.e. leader and clan heroes, are
in control of the channel, and are responsible for what is said on it.
Therefore, it is up to them to use this command when necessary. A clan member
who has been noclanchanned can still see what other clan members say, unless
he turns the channel off.
~



96 CLANSET~
Syntax: clanset {+/-}  <player> <clan>
        clanset leader <player>

Immortals can use this to add or remove a player's clan membership. 
They can also use it to make a clan member a leader. Please use this
only under special circumstances, eg. if the former leader of a clan
has left the clan, or immed or whatever :)

Note: don't use this to member or demember a player's clan status.
That is something which only clan leaders should do and immortals
should respect the decisions of clan leaders as to who joins their
clan or not.
~


1 'DISCIPLES OF THE WYRM' WYRM~
|W
The Book of the Wyrm
|w
   Of  all  the races  that  of dragon  is the most  ancient on Xania.
Before the  creation of Xania, before  the universe was forged, before
the  immortals  were born,  even before  the   beginning of time there
existed the Great Wyrm. 

   Before  the dawn of time  the Great Wyrm  was  all that existed. He
lingered  in  an  eternal  slumber  and  experienced   a  multitude of
dreams. These  dreams became more and  more vivid  and real until they
began to take on physical forms. Thus in the silence and darkness, the
immortals were born.  The Great Wyrm watched the immortals antics with
amusement.....until they created Xania. 

   Soon after their world   took shape, the immortals discovered  that
their bounty was tainted with evil. This worried the great dragon, for
he found that  his  dreams were  disturbed by  horrifying  images.  He
could  feel another consciousness slowly  forming, which could perhaps
gain power to rival his own.  After great deliberation, the Great Wyrm
decided that  he must  make others in  his own  form, who would embody
virtue  and power.  He would create  beings who  would carry forth the
rites of the Wyrm. So the dragons of Xania were born. 

   The most ancient of all the dragons was Samael,  and the Great Wyrm
appeared to  his disciple and taught him  of the virtues  that he must
uphold.  The  first   was  that  he must    crush all  evil   that  he
encountered.  Secondly,  he was to  help all those of good intentions,
in order to ward against the encroachment of evil and chaos.  Thirdly,
he was instructed to protect the weak  from injustice. Finally, he was
to  spread the word of  the Wyrm to others  and gather about him those
who embody the spirit of the dragon, whether  they possess the body of
a dragon or not. 

   And so the Disciples of the Wyrm  were founded, a great temple hewn
from ancient rock and  the timeless task of   upholding the wishes  of
Great Wyrm begun. 

See help on: |WWyrmlore, Wyrmjoin|w

~
1 WYRMLORE~
|W
The Writings of Samael
|w
...It has been many millenia since I was taught  the virtues.  In this
time we have  amassed  many believers and   the corporeal form  of the
Great Wyrm has strengthened.  We have fought against darkness wherever
we have  found it.  But  even our  own clan  members, and perhaps even
myself, are not immune to the corruptions of evil. 

   Some dragons have been known to become so contaminated by evil that
they have  opposed the Disciplehood  of the Wyrm. Others were infected
in a more subtle way and  have worked to pervert the  clan. It is they
who believed  not  in the  virtues,  but  rather in the   supremacy of
dragons over all of the other races,  to some extent that continues to
the present day.   Many dragons consider  the  other races as  nothing
more that cattle for them to feast upon. 

   Fortunately, most  of   the dragons where  able   to  withstand the
darkness and uphold the virtues of the  Great Wyrm. A great temple was
built by such a  band of dragons,  using a solid  block of white stone
and  was imbued with magical essence  from the Great  Wyrm himself.  A
dungeon  was built with puzzles and  creatures to  challenge those who
would seek  to join the  clan:  to discover whether  they were  strong
enough to maintain the strict laws of the Wyrm. 

   After  the temple was  built, we were approached by  a band of dark
elves, known as  the Elves of  Narion.  With diplomacy  they requested
entry, saying that  they wished to learn more  of the teachings of the
Great Wyrm. We welcomed  them  gladly, rejoicing  that so many  people
wished  to embrace  our   virtues.  Alas,  the   elves  bore us   evil
intentions; they were misguided and believed that we followed the path
of  our evil   breathen who  fed  upon  them,  and  in our sleep  they
slaughtered my  brothers.  Overcome with anger,   I entered a  fury of
revenge which I now  regret. Using the height of  my powers,  I called
for the Great Wyrm from his eternal slumber in the  hope that he might
protect his   followers from harm.  The   revenge was  spectacular and
frightening. In an instance the elves grew old  and withered until all
that remained was dust blowing in the wind. 

   It has taken time,  but  I have found  new  followers and we   have
restored   our  temple.  We  are  again  upholding   the virtues,  and
spreading the  word of the  Wyrm. Some animosity still  exists between
dragons and elves; alas it seems  that neither will ever fully forgive
the other.... 

See help on: |WDisciples, Wyrmjoin|w
~

1 WYRMJOIN~
The Disciples of  the Wyrm  are essentially,  a class  who uphold  the
virtues of  their God, the Great Wyrm.  There aligned towards goodness
and law,  and will therefore purge sources  of evil and chaos whenever
they are given the opportunity. 

To join this clan, you must speak to  the Preceptor of the Great Wyrm.
He will look into your heart and see whether you are worthy enough to 
undertake the labours that this clan established for itself, centuries
ago. 

